{{ phase_description }}

## Directory Contents

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `requirements.md` | Product requirements — one `## REQ-XXX` section per requirement |
| `architecture.md` | Technical context consumed by `req-decompose` during issue expansion |
| `manifest.json` | Auto-generated by `req-decompose create` — maps REQ IDs to GitHub issue numbers |

## Workflow

### 1. Author requirements

Fill in `requirements.md` with one `## REQ-XXX: Title` section per requirement.
Fill in `architecture.md` with the technical context for this phase.

### 2. Preview with scan

```
/req-decompose scan .
```

Review the preview. Refine `requirements.md` and `architecture.md` until:
- Each issue body preview is clear and actionable
- Open questions are intentional (things humans genuinely need to decide)
- Dependencies between requirements are correct

### 3. Create issues

```
/req-decompose create .
```

Creates one GitHub issue per requirement. Requirements with zero open questions
and no dependencies are automatically labeled `claude-ready`. All others get
`needs-refinement`.

### 4. Human review

Review each `needs-refinement` issue on GitHub. Answer the open questions by
editing the issue body. Add the `claude-ready` label when the issue is ready
for automated development.

### 5. Track progress

```
/req-decompose status .
```

Shows current state of all phase issues and their position in the pipeline.

## Labels

| Label | Applied by | Meaning |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| `needs-refinement` | `req-decompose create` | Issue needs human review of open questions |
| `claude-ready` | Human (or auto if zero open questions) | Ready for dev-loop |
| `blocked` | `req-decompose create` | Has unresolved requirement dependencies |
| `dev-loop-active` | dev-loop agent | Automated development in progress |
| `dev-loop-review` | dev-loop agent | PR submitted, awaiting human review |
